Ps>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T172238Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=221\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 221\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Environmental Defense published a list of the organizations that have questioned global warming and climate change to which Exxon \'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Environmental Defense published a list of the organizations that have questioned global warming and climate change to which Exxon </title>\n  <description>\n    Environmental Defense published a list of the organizations that have questioned global warming and climate change to which Exxon funneled money.  Exxon has poured millions of dollars into funding &quot;junk science&quot; around the world. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 221</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=221</url><date>20111024164348</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Environmental Defense</link-text><url>http://www.environmentaldefense.org/article.cfm?ContentID=4870</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.exxon.mobil.com</link-text><url>http://www.exxon.mobil.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>exxon company, u.s.a.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Exxon</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0077162</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Exxon Company, U.S.A.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Exxon</tagged>\n      <address>TX\n5959 Las Colinas Blvd\n75039\nIrving\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0077162</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T172245Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=226\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 226\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Ford was rated as the 18th worst polluter on the Political Economy Research Institute\\\'s (PERI) Toxic 100 index.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Ford was rated as the 18th worst polluter on the Political Economy Research Institute\'s (PERI) Toxic 100 index.</title>\n  <description>\n    Ford was rated as the 18th worst polluter on the Political Economy Research Institute\'s (PERI) Toxic 100 index. PERI is an “independent unit of the University of Massachusetts,” that promotes environmental sustainability and human rights through research. The index is based on 2007 EPA Toxics Release Inventory data. PERI\'s Toxic 100 index ranks the nation\'s largest companies based on the quantity of their emissions, relative toxicity of chemicals emitted, and proximity to population centers, among other criteria. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 226</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=226</url><date>20111024164349</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Political Economy Research Institute (PERI)</link-text><url>http://http://www.peri.umass.edu/Toxic-100-Index.430.0.html</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.ford.com</link-text><url>http://www.ford.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>ford motor co/parts   service</normalized>\n      <tagged>Ford</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0031508</GCP>\n<GCP>0084422</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>ford motor company/special vehicle oper.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Ford</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0756122</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T172253Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=221\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 221\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"Exxon-Mobil was ranked the fifth \\x{201c}greenest\\x{201d} oil company out of the top 10 leading US oil corporations by Greenopia in 2011.\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Exxon-Mobil was ranked the fifth “greenest” oil company out of the top 10 leading US oil corporations by Greenopia in 2011.</title>\n  <description>\n    Exxon-Mobil was ranked the fifth “greenest” oil company out of the top 10 leading US oil corporations by Greenopia in 2011. Exxon publishes a decent sustainability report but the data for oil spill volume is not included. Greenopia also commends Exxon’s relatively low water consumption involved in its oil production and notes that Exxon has had a “very small” number of spills in regards to the volume of its oil production. However, Greenopia criticizes Exxon’s massive production of greenhouse gas emissions, even when scaled to production as Exxon’s is the largest oil company. This year’s emissions are significantly lower than 2008 but Exxon still produces a lot of waste, even when scaled against production. Exxon has been recently accused for a spill in Brooklyn, New York that was larger in the total amount of oil spilled than the Exxon Valdez, as this spill is estimated at 17-30 million gallons versus the Valdez’s 11 million; the spill has been taking place from the 1800s to 1900s and Exxon has not done anything to address it. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    \n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 221</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=221</url><date>20111024164349</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Greenopia</link-text><url>http://http://www.greenopia.com/usa/oil_listing.aspx?ID=6&amp;input=Name-or-product&amp;Listpage=0 </url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>exxon company, u.s.a.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Exxon</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0077162</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Exxon Company, U.S.A.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Exxon</tagged>\n      <address>TX\n5959 Las Colinas Blvd\n75039\nIrving\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0077162</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T172300Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=400\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 400\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"\\x{2022} Delta Air Lines, Inc is a member of the International Air Transport Association (IATA), a global group of airlines and airports.\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>• Delta Air Lines, Inc is a member of the International Air Transport Association (IATA), a global group of airlines and airports.</title>\n  <description>\n    • Delta Air Lines, Inc is a member of the International Air Transport Association (IATA), a global group of airlines and airports.  The IATA has staunchly opposed plans for a carbon emissions trading system in the European Union that could reduce greenhouse gas emissions and mitigate the effects of global climate change.  The organization has argued that such a scheme would be prohibitively expensive for the airlines and make it more difficult to retain profits. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 400</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=400</url><date>20111024164349</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>New York Times</link-text><url>http://greeninc.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/02/11/curbing-foreign-airline-emissions-in-europe/</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.delta.com</link-text><url>http://www.delta.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Delta Air Lines</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T172305Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=291\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 291\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Christine Drake, a Seattle woman with psychiatric disabilities, is charging Starbucks Coffee Co.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Christine Drake, a Seattle woman with psychiatric disabilities, is charging Starbucks Coffee Co.</title>\n  <description>\n    Christine Drake, a Seattle woman with psychiatric disabilities, is charging Starbucks Coffee Co. with decreasing her hours, berating her in front of customers, and failing to accommodate her special needs before firing her in 2004. The US Equal Employment Opportunity Commission is requesting Starbucks to pay Drake $40,000 in lost wages.  Should the case go before a jury, Starbucks could pay up to $300,000 in compensatory and punitive damages. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 291</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=291</url><date>20111024164350</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Seattle Post-Intelligencer</link-text><url>http://seattlepi.nwsource.com/business/285189_starbucks15.html</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.starbucks.com</link-text><url>http://www.starbucks.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>starbucks coffee company</normalized>\n      <tagged>Starbucks</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0762111</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>starbucks coffee company</normalized>\n      <tagged>Starbucks Coffee Co.</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0762111</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>starbucks coffee company</normalized>\n      <tagged>Starbucks Coffee Co.</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0762111</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T172335Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=306\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 306\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'According to the International Labor Rights Fund (ILRF), Wal-Mart workers from around the world came together to sue Wal-Mart in a\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>According to the International Labor Rights Fund (ILRF), Wal-Mart workers from around the world came together to sue Wal-Mart in a</title>\n  <description>\n    According to the International Labor Rights Fund (ILRF), Wal-Mart workers from around the world came together to sue Wal-Mart in a California Superior Court on September 13, 2005, citing a wide range of labor abuses.  Plaintiffs in the case included men and women from California, Bangladesh, China, Indonesia, Nicaragua, and Swaziland who recounted numerous violations of international labor standards under the responsibility of Wal-Mart.  \r\n&lt;p&gt;\r\nThe ILRF claims that Wal-Mart “failed to meet its contractual duty to ensure that its suppliers pay basic wages due; forced [workers] to work excessive hours seven days a week with no time off for holidays; obstructed [workers’] attempts to form a union; and, made false and misleading statements to the American public about the company’s labor and human rights practices.” \r\n&lt;p&gt;\r\nAccording to the ILRF, Wal-Mart presents foreign suppliers with a Supplier Standards Agreement that makes compliance with Wal-Mart’s corporate code of conduct a prerequisite for any supplier-purchaser relationship. The code of conduct inclusion is intended to serve as a built-in protection for workers at foreign factories.  Workers have the right to enforce these standards if employers fail to do so, and the ILRF states that the governments of countries represented in this case lack the necessary legal infrastructure to adequately redress grievances related to labor abuses. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Business Practices | Workers Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 306</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=306</url><date>20111024164350</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>International Labor Rights Fund</link-text><url>http://www.laborrights.org/projects/corporate/walmart/WalMartComplaint091305.pdf</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>wal-mart stores, inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Wal-Mart</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0078742</GCP>\n<GCP>0605388</GCP>\n<GCP>0681131</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Wal-Mart Stores, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Wal-Mart</tagged>\n      <address>AR\n702 S.W. 8th St\nMS 16\n72716 \nBentonville\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0078742</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Wal-Mart Stores, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Wal-Mart</tagged>\n      <address>AR\n702 S.W. 8th St\nMS 16\n72716 \nBentonville\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0078742</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Wal-Mart Stores, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Wal-Mart</tagged>\n      <address>AR\n702 S.W. 8th St\nMS 16\n72716 \nBentonville\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0078742</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Wal-Mart Stores, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Wal-Mart</tagged>\n      <address>AR\n702 S.W. 8th St\nMS 16\n72716 \nBentonville\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0078742</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Wal-Mart Stores, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Wal-Mart</tagged>\n      <address>AR\n702 S.W. 8th St\nMS 16\n72716 \nBentonville\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0078742</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Wal-Mart Stores, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Wal-Mart</tagged>\n      <address>AR\n702 S.W. 8th St\nMS 16\n72716 \nBentonville\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0078742</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T172357Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=243\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 243\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'According to the nonprofit investigative journalism group the Center for Public Integrity, IBM is responsible for 28 current or fo\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>According to the nonprofit investigative journalism group the Center for Public Integrity, IBM is responsible for 28 current or fo</title>\n  <description>\n    According to the nonprofit investigative journalism group the Center for Public Integrity, IBM is responsible for 28 current or former Superfund sites. Superfund sites are locations designated by the Environmental Protection Agency as being so contaminated by toxic chemicals that they are dangerous to human health. Companies found responsible for superfund sites are required to either pay for the cleanup personally, or to pay the Environmental Protection Agency to conduct the cleanup. IBM, which is designated as bearing full responsibility for one site, and shared responsibility for 27 others, has only successfully cleaned up 2 sites since the Superfund law was passed in 1980. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 243</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=243</url><date>20111024164351</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Center for Public Integrity</link-text><url>http://projects.publicintegrity.org/Superfund/SiteResults.aspx?act=IBM</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.ibm.com</link-text><url>http://www.ibm.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>IBM Corporation</normalized>\n      <tagged>IBM</tagged>\n      <address>NY\n1 New Orchard Rd.\n10504-1722 \nArmonk\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0883436</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>IBM Corporation</normalized>\n      <tagged>IBM</tagged>\n      <address>NY\n1 New Orchard Rd.\n10504-1722 \nArmonk\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0883436</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T172401Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=281\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 281\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"An Oxfam International report called \\x{201c}Offside! Labour Rights and Sportswear Production in Asia,\\x{201d} examines how twelve international\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>An Oxfam International report called “Offside! Labour Rights and Sportswear Production in Asia,” examines how twelve international</title>\n  <description>\n    An Oxfam International report called “Offside! Labour Rights and Sportswear Production in Asia,” examines how twelve international sports brands are confronting worker rights issues in factories, particularly the right to form and join trade unions. Reebok acted swiftly and decisively in response to violations of trade union workers’ rights in Factories A and B, two Indonesian factories that workers wish to remain unnamed. Reebok worked in partnership with labor rights organizations, promptly launching an investigation upon hearing trade union workers’ complaints. The company applied pressure to its suppliers for workers’ rights compliance, expressed concern over the number of temporary workers, and continuously assisted workers with its human rights staff. Such actions have compelled the management at Factory A to terminate its business relationship with Reebok.\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;While Reebok has a record of supporting trade unionists, Oxfam International challenges the corporation to examine this issue on a global scale. Oxfam urges Reebok to:\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Properly investigate allegations of discrimination against trade union members, especially in nations where the courts and government are under-resourced&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Increase transparency to ensure their buying practices do not have negative impacts on workers and their right to organize&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt; \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Business Practices | Workers Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 281</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=281</url><date>20111024164352</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Oxfam</link-text><url>http://www.oxfam.org/en/files/offside_labor_report/download</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.reebok.com</link-text><url>http://www.reebok.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>reebok international, ltd.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Reebok</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0054871</GCP>\n<GCP>0601352</GCP>\n<GCP>0611368</GCP>\n<GCP>0630994</GCP>\n<GCP>0638192</GCP>\n<GCP>0647201</GCP>\n<GCP>0650789</GCP>\n<GCP>0656344</GCP>\n<GCP>0664712</GCP>\n<GCP>0688359</GCP>\n<GCP>0690174</GCP>\n<GCP>0703518</GCP>\n<GCP>0713732</GCP>\n<GCP>0722977</GCP>\n<GCP>0760617</GCP>\n<GCP>0785729</GCP>\n<GCP>0803675</GCP>\n<GCP>0827066</GCP>\n<GCP>0882561</GCP>\n<GCP>0882728</GCP>\n<