  \'At the end of 2008, GlaxoSmithKline announced that it would no longer be spending corporate money on political contributions.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>At the end of 2008, GlaxoSmithKline announced that it would no longer be spending corporate money on political contributions.</title>\n  <description>\n    At the end of 2008, GlaxoSmithKline announced that it would no longer be spending corporate money on political contributions.  During the 2008 campaigns, the company provided over $585,000 in donations to political candidates in the United States.  CEO Andrew Witty said that the decision was made in order to increase corporate transparency and to get rid of the idea that political contributions give pharmaceutical companies special privileges.  The move will not apply to individual employees’ donations, nor to the political action committee run by employees. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 390</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=390</url><date>20111024164353</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Wall Street Journal</link-text><url>http://online.wsj.com/article/SB122999215468528539.html</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.gsk.com</link-text><url>http://www.gsk.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>glaxosmithkline consumer healthcare, lp.</normalized>\n      <tagged>GlaxoSmithKline</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0053100</GCP>\n<GCP>0074684</GCP>\n<GCP>0307660</GCP>\n<GCP>0307661</GCP>\n<GCP>0307662</GCP>\n<GCP>0307663</GCP>\n<GCP>0307665</GCP>\n<GCP>0307667</GCP>\n<GCP>0311530</GCP>\n<GCP>0345800</GCP>\n<GCP>0349692</GCP>\n<GCP>0353100</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>glaxosmithkline plc</normalized>\n    