lion dollar settlement for violations of labor laws and international human rights standards on the island of Saipan, which is part of the U.S. Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands.  Workers reported working 12 hours a day, seven days a week for less than $3.05 an hour.  They also reported signing &quot;shadow contracts&quot; that waived many basic human rights. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Business Practices | Workers Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 244</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=244</url><date>20111024164353</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Clean Clothes Campaign</link-text><url>http://www.cleanclothes.org/legal/04-01-08.htm</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.jcrew.com</link-text><url>http://www.jcrew.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>J. Crew</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T172734Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=291\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 291\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"The Ethisphere Institute is a New York City based think tank that annually releases a non-ranked list of \\x{201c}The World\\x{2019}s Most Ethical\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>The Ethisphere Institute is a New York City based think tank that annually releases a non-ranked list of “The World’s Most Ethical</title>\n  <description>\n    The Ethisphere Institute is a New York City based think tank that annually releases a non-ranked list of “The World’s Most Ethical Companies.” Starbucks has appeared on the list for all four years, in addition to Google, General Electric and 33 other companies. New 2010 additions include Ford Motor Company and Campbell Soup. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 291</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=291</url><date>20111024164354</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>ABC News</link-text><url>http://abcnews.go.com/Business/starbucks-ford-google-worlds-ethical-companies/story?id=10184891 </url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>campbell soup company</normalized>\n      <tagged>Campbell Soup</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0051000</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>ford motor co/parts   service</normalized>\n      <tagged>Ford Motor Company</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0031508</GCP>\n<GCP>0084422</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>ford motor company/special vehicle oper.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Ford Motor Company</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0756122</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Ford Motor Company, S.A. De C.V.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Ford Motor Company</tagged>\n      <address>Av. Paseo De La Reforma No.333\nCol. Cuauhtemoc\n06500\nMexico City, D.F.\nMexico</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0714512</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Ford Motor Company/special Vehicle Oper.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Ford Motor Company</tagged>\n      <address>MI\n1700 Southfield Road\n48101\nAllan Park\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0756122</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>general electric company</normalized>\n      <tagged>General Electric</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0043168</GCP>\n<GCP>0783166</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>starbucks coffee company</normalized>\n      <tagged>Starbucks</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0762111</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T172804Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=390\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 390\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In 2002, information surfaced on clinical trials undertaken by GlaxoSmithKline in its testing of the efficacy of the anti-depressa\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In 2002, information surfaced on clinical trials undertaken by GlaxoSmithKline in its testing of the efficacy of the anti-depressa</title>\n  <description>\n    In 2002, information surfaced on clinical trials undertaken by GlaxoSmithKline in its testing of the efficacy of the anti-depressant Paxil in children.  Worldwide, hundreds of children participated in three different studies, each involving two groups:  one receiving Paxil, the other receiving a placebo.  In the end, Paxil proved to be no more effective than the placebo.  In the largest trial, Study 329, seven children developed side effects so serious that they needed to be hospitalized.  Significantly more children taking Paxil attempted suicide or self-harm on the drug than the placebo.  When the company discovered these results, it brought in experts to bury the negative test results and ghost-write scientific articles claiming that Paxil was safe and effective in children.  The drug is now banned in the UK and carries a black-box suicide risk label in the United States. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Human Rights | Health and Wellness</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 390</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=390</url><date>20111024164355</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>CorpWatch</link-text><url>http://www.corpwatch.org/article.php?id=14606</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>glaxosmithkline consumer healthcare, lp.</normalized>\n      <tagged>GlaxoSmithKline</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0053100</GCP>\n<GCP>0074684</GCP>\n<GCP>0307660</GCP>\n<GCP>0307661</GCP>\n<GCP>0307662</GCP>\n<GCP>0307663</GCP>\n<GCP>0307665</GCP>\n<GCP>0307667</GCP>\n<GCP>0311530</GCP>\n<GCP>0345800</GCP>\n<GCP>0349692</GCP>\n<GCP>0353100</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>glaxosmithkline plc</normalized>\n      <tagged>GlaxoSmithKline</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>5000124</GCP>\n<GCP>5000134</GCP>\n<GCP>5000198</GCP>\n<GCP>5000199</GCP>\n<GCP>5000347</GCP>\n<GCP>5000483</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>glaxosmithkline australia pty ltd</normalized>\n      <tagged>GlaxoSmithKline</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>9300673</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>glaxosmithkline consumer healthcare sdn bhd</normalized>\n      <tagged>GlaxoSmithKline</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>9556019</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>glaxosmithkline consumer healthcare</normalized>\n      <tagged>GlaxoSmithKline</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>9403099</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Glaxosmithkline Consumer Healthcare,