11024164356</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Business Wire</link-text><url>http://www.businesswire.com/portal/site/home/permalink/?ndmViewId=news_view&amp;newsId=20100610005051&amp;newsLang=en</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.humana.com </link-text><url>http://www.humana.com </url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Humana USA Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Humana</tagged>\n      <address>NV\n1475 Terminal Way, Suite E\n89502\nReno\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0681110</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T173036Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=402\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 402\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"\\x{2022} In late 2006, US Airways barred six Muslim clerics from a Minneapolis-to-Phoenix flight.\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>• In late 2006, US Airways barred six Muslim clerics from a Minneapolis-to-Phoenix flight.</title>\n  <description>\n    • In late 2006, US Airways barred six Muslim clerics from a Minneapolis-to-Phoenix flight.  The imams, who had prayed on their prayer rugs prior to boarding the flight, were removed from the plane after a passenger told a flight attendant that he was alarmed by their behavior.  The men were then handcuffed, detained and questioned.  Company officials also stated that the passenger overheard them making what he thought were anti-American statements.  Flight attendants consulted with local law enforcement and the FBI, who decided that the men posed a security risk. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Human Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 402</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=402</url><date>20111024164357</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Washington Post</link-text><url>http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/11/27/AR2006112701184.html</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.usairways.com</link-text><url>http://www.usairways.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>US Airways</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T173121Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=185\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 185\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'The State Department of Environmental Conservation fined Hess Corporation $1.1 million in February 2008 for petroleum storage viol\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>The State Department of Environmental Conservation fined Hess Corporation $1.1 million in February 2008 for petroleum storage viol</title>\n  <description>\n    The State Department of Environmental Conservation fined Hess Corporation $1.1 million in February 2008 for petroleum storage violations. The agreement also entails $300,000 of funding for a wetlands restoration project and the clean up of 65 gas stations and oil storage facilities in New York City and the Hudson Valley. The violations, tracing back to the 1990s and early 2000s, concern noncompliance with storage regulations as well as the restoration of a bulkhead without proper permits. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 185</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=185</url><date>20111024164357</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>New York Sun</link-text><url>http://http://www.nysun.com/new-york/hess-must-pay-11-million-fine-for-environmental/72084/</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.hess.com</link-text><url>http://www.hess.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>amerada hess corporation</normalized>\n      <tagged>Hess Corporation</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0729071</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Amerada Hess Corporation</normalized>\n      <tagged>Hess Corporation</tagged>\n      <address>NJ\n1 Hess Plaza\n07095-0961\nWoodbridge\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0729071</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T173211Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=197\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 197\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In February 2005 the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission (EEOC) filed a lawsuit against Burger King on behalf of a 16 year-old\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In February 2005 the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission (EEOC) filed a lawsuit against Burger King on behalf of a 16 year-old</title>\n  <description>\n    In February 2005 the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission (EEOC) filed a lawsuit against Burger King on behalf of a 16 year-old former employee who claimed she was fired after refusing the store manager\'s repeated requests for sex. According to the lawsuit, the teenager started working at a Milwaukee Burger King in January 2003 and refused the store manager\'s requests for sex. In September 2003, she was fired after making plans to complain about the harassment to some of the company\'s managers who were scheduled to visit the restaurant, the lawsuit said.&lt;p&gt;The lawsuit seeks a court order reinstating Merriweather to her job, back pay\r\nand compensatory and punitive damages up to $300,000, said Jean Kamp, an EEOC\r\nattorney.\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The manager who fired Merriweather is in his mid-30s and still works at the\r\nrestaurant, Kamp said. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Human Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 197</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=197</url><date>20111024164357</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>WAGE Project</link-text><url>http://www.wageproject.org/content/news/</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.burgerking.com</link-text><url>http://www.burgerking.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>burger king corporation</normalized>\n      <tagged>Burger King</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0675258</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T174221Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=367\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 367\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"\\x{2022} Sprint Nextel was named by Ethisphere Institute as having one of the best ethics program overall.\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>• Sprint Nextel was named by Ethisphere Institute as having one of the best ethics program overall.</title>\n  <description>\n    • Sprint Nextel was named by Ethisphere Institute as having one of the best ethics program overall. Ranking companies’ ethics programs from excellent to unsatisfactory. Sprint Nextel received the &quot;above standard&quot; rating meaning the corporation has “strong programs that exceed all government standards,&quot; as well as meet most of the criteria that Ethisphere Institutite requires in their evalaution. In addition, an &quot;above average&quot; rank means that the company could meet the other criteria with a few simple changes. Ethisphere Institute is an international think tank committed to promoting “business ethics, corporate social responsibility, anti-corruption and sustainability.” \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 367</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=367</url><date>20111024164358</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Ethisphere Institute</link-text><url>http://www.ethisphere.com/best-ethics-programs-overall-government-contractors/</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.sprint.com</link-text><url>http://www.sprint.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>sprint nextel corporation</normalized>\n      <tagged>Sprint Nextel</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0639381</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T174308Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=189\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 189\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'According to the Social Investment Research Analyst Network, ten years after the Federal Glass Ceiling Commission recommended disc\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>According to the Social Investment Research Analyst Network, ten years after the Federal Glass Ceiling Commission recommended disc</title>\n  <description>\n    According to the Social Investment Research Analyst Network, ten years after the Federal Glass Ceiling Commission recommended disclosure of diversity data as a way to remove barriers and promote women and minority advancement, most US companies still fail to voluntarily disclose EEO data to the public.  Avon is listed as one of the companies that does not provide full public disclosure.  Rather, disclosure of EEO data is made upon request. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 189</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=189</url><date>20111024164358</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Social Investment Research Analyst Network (SIRAN)</link-text><url>http://www.siran.org/eeo1.php</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.avon.com</link-text><url>http://www.avon.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Avon</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T174410Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=208&MajorSub=1&CompanyName=Dodge\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 208\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In January of 2006, Chrysler announced layoffs of 6,000 employees to take place in March of that year, including 20 percent of gen\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In January of 2006, Chrysler announced layoffs of 6,000 employees to take place in March of that year, including 20 percent of gen</title>\n  <description>\n    In January of 2006, Chrysler announced layoffs of 6,000 employees to take place in March of that year, including 20 percent of general and administrative staff and 30 percent of management. Said Dieter Zetsche, Chrysler\'s Chairman of the Board, &quot;Our objective in taking these actions is to create a lean, agile structure, with streamlined and stable processes that will unleash Chrysler\'s full potential.&quot; \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Business Practices | Workers Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 208</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=208&amp;MajorSub=1&amp;CompanyName=Dodge</url><date>20111024164358</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>www.chrysler.com</link-text><url>http://www.chrysler.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Chrysler</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T174551Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=207\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 207\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In January 2004, Christian Brothers Investment Services urged Costco shareholders to demand that the company publicly disclose its\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In January 2004, Christian Brothers Investment Services urged Costco shareholders to demand that the company publicly disclose its</title>\n  <description>\n    In January 2004, Christian Brothers Investment Services urged Costco shareholders to demand that the company publicly disclose its land procurement policies at the annual shareholders meeting. Costco has previously lacked a stated policy for land procurement and use. Its practices in such locations as Cuernavaca, Mexico, Cypress, Ca. and other sites in the U.S. have led to the criticism of social, human rights and environmental groups.  (see related items) \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 207</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=207</url><date>20111024164358</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>PR Newswire</link-text><url>http://www.cbisonline.com/page.asp?id=102</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.costco.com</link-text><url>http://www.costco.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>costco companies inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Costco</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0096619</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Costco Companies Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Costco</tagged>\n      <address>WA\n999 Lake Drive\n98027\nIssaquah\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0096619</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T174618Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=254&MajorSub=1&CompanyName=Ralphs%20Grocery%20Company\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 254\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Kroger does not attempt to avoid biotech ingredients, citing the federal government position that genetically engineered foods are\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Kroger does not attempt to avoid biotech ingredients, citing the federal government position that genetically engineered foods are</title>\n  <description>\n    Kroger does not attempt to avoid biotech ingredients, citing the federal government position that genetically engineered foods are safe and require no labeling. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Human Rights | Health and Wellness</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 254</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=254&amp;MajorSub=1&amp;CompanyName=Ralphs%20Grocery%20Company</url><date>20111024164359</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>www.kroger.com</link-text><url>http://www.kroger.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>The Kroger Co.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Kroger</tagged>\n      <address>OH\n1014 Vine Street\n45202\nCincinnati\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0686924</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T174748Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=266\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => 