nizing around the meatpacking i</title>\n  <description>\n    With the increased activism surrounding immigrant rights, there was a series of demonstrations organizing around the meatpacking industry in cities such as Washington DC, Boston, New York, Raleigh, Richmond, and Chicago. Specifically, organizers targeted Smithfield Foods, the nation\'s largest meatpacker. A diverse coalition of groups including DC Jobs with Justice, Campaign for Labor Rights, and United Food and Commercial Workers, highlighted the dangerous working conditions in the world\'s largest pork processing facility in Tar Heel, North Carolina.  Working conditions have not improved since the 2002 lawsuit that found the company guilty of violating human rights in Tar Heel, NC. (Please see related alert item under “Unionization,” citing Feedstuff.) \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Business Practices | Workers Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 289</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=289&amp;MajorSub=1&amp;CompanyName=Yano</url><date>20111024164404</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>US Newswire</link-text><url>http://www.releases.usnewswire.com/GetRelease.asp?id=67754</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.smithfieldfoods.com</link-text><url>http://www.smithfieldfoods.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Smithfield Foods Inc</normalized>\n      <tagged>Smithfield Foods</tagged>\n      <address>IL\n5533 W. Cermak Road\n60650\nCicero\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0075932</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T180624Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=284&MajorSub=1&CompanyName=Tom%20Thumb\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 284\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In January 2004, in the wake of worker strikes over health care benefits, Safeway Inc.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In January 2004, in the wake of worker strikes over health care benefits, Safeway Inc.</title>\n  <description>\n    In January 2004, in the wake of worker strikes over health care benefits, Safeway Inc. awarded 11 senior and executive vice presidents millions of dollars in stock grants and options under a new compensation plan.  When Labor leaders and union representatives criticized this decision, a Safeway spokesperson responded that the awards were necessary because &quot;after two years of wage freezes and undersized bonuses, it was becoming difficult to attract and keep talent. &quot; \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 284</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=284&amp;MajorSub=1&amp;CompanyName=Tom%20Thumb</url><date>20111024164404</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>www.safeway.com</link-text><url>http://www.safeway.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>safeway, inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Safeway</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0076750</GCP>\n<GCP>0321130</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T180710Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=440\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 440\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"Hilton Hotel in Los Angeles allegedly failed to pay temporary worker\\x{2019}s livable wages.\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Hilton Hotel in Los Angeles allegedly failed to pay temporary worker’s livable wages.</title>\n  <description>\n    Hilton Hotel in Los Angeles allegedly failed to pay temporary worker’s livable wages.  Two housekeepers filed for a law suit on June 15, 2010 claiming that workers hired by Hilton were not getting paid the minimal amount required by the city. According to the article by Business Journal, the Los Angeles hotel had original tried to challenge the new law requiring them to pay the livable wage which is $10.30 per hour with insurance benefits or $11.35 per hour without insurance benefits. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Business Practices | Workers Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 440</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=440</url><date>20111024164405</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Business Journal</link-text><url>http://www.labusinessjournal.com/news/2010/jun/16/wages-lawsuit-targets-lax-hilton/</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.hiltonworldwide.com</link-text><url>http://www.hiltonworldwide.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Hilton</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Hilton Hotel</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T180749Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=288\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 288\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Announced in 1998, the Cuiaba pipeline in South America has been controversial from the onset.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Announced in 1998, the Cuiaba pipeline in South America has been controversial from the onset.</title>\n  <description>\n    Announced in 1998, the Cuiaba pipeline in South America has been controversial from the onset. Running through Bolivia\'s Chiquitano Tropical Forest, the 390 mile long natural gas pipeline was built by the now infamous Enron and is partly owned by Shell is part owner of the Cuiaba pipeline in South America. The pipeline has substantially affected indigenous communities that reside in the region surrounding the pipeline, threatened more than 90 endangered species living in the forest, and has led to an increase in illegal logging and poaching.  Indigenous communities, NGOs and even the governments of the countries affected proposed alternative routes for the pipeline, but Enron and Shell claimed they would be too costly. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 288</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=288</url><date>20111024164405</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Amazon Watch</link-text><url>http://http://www.amazonwatch.org/amazon/BO/cuiaba/index.php?page_number=1</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.shell.com</link-text><url>http://www.shell.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Enron</tagged>\n 