spx</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.continental.com</link-text><url>http://www.continental.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Continental Airlines, Inc./chelsea Catering Division</normalized>\n      <tagged>Continental Air</tagged>\n      <address>CO\n27550 E. 75th Avenue\n80249\nDenver\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0663209</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T195508Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=391\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 391\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In 2006, two men filed separate lawsuits against Pfizer for not issuing adequate warnings about the possible side effects of the c\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In 2006, two men filed separate lawsuits against Pfizer for not issuing adequate warnings about the possible side effects of the c</title>\n  <description>\n    In 2006, two men filed separate lawsuits against Pfizer for not issuing adequate warnings about the possible side effects of the cholesterol-lowering drug Lipitor.  Each claimed that they suffered from memory loss, pain, and muscle weakness as a result of taking the drug.  A spokesman for Pfizer stated that all side effects are listed on its labeling and usually mentioned in commercials.  He also said that the symptoms experienced by the plaintiffs were very rare, occurring in less than one percent of patients.  Mark Krum, the lawyer who filed the suits, replied by saying that the rarity of the symptoms did not excuse Pfizer from marketing the drug more responsibly. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Human Rights | Health and Wellness</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 391</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=391</url><date>20111024164427</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Law.com</link-text><url>http://www.law.com/jsp/article.jsp?id=1149843918824</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>pfizer inc./consumer health care</normalized>\n      <tagged>Pfizer</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0074300</GCP>\n<GCP>0086414</GCP>\n<GCP>0305012</GCP>\n<GCP>0305013</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>pfizer inc./pfipharmecs div</normalized>\n      <tagged>Pfizer</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0071404</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>pfizer inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Pfizer</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0087219</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>pfizer consumer healthcare</normalized>\n      <tagged>Pfizer</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>9310059</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>pfizer consumer health products company</normalized>\n      <tagged>Pfizer</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>5010123</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>pfizer pty ltd</normalized>\n      <tagged>Pfizer</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>9313212</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Pfizer Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Pfizer</tagged>\n      <address>NY\n235 E 42nd St\n10017 \nNew York\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0087219</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Pfizer Inc./Pfipharmecs Div</normalized>\n      <tagged>Pfizer</tagged>\n      <address>MO\n1 SE Pfizer Way\n64081 \nLees Summit\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0071404</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Pfizer Consumer Healthcare</normalized>\n      <tagged>Pfizer</tagged>\n      <address>NY\n235 East 42nd St.\n10017 \nNew York\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>030573</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T195638Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=394\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 394\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In January 2008, a class-action lawsuit was filed against Sanofi-Aventis on behalf of everyone who purchased Sanofi securities bet\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In January 2008, a class-action lawsuit was filed against Sanofi-Aventis on behalf of everyone who purchased Sanofi securities bet</title>\n  <description>\n    In January 2008, a class-action lawsuit was filed against Sanofi-Aventis on behalf of everyone who purchased Sanofi securities between February 17, 2006 through June 13, 2007.  Schiffrin Barroway Topaz &amp; Kessler, the law firm bringing the case, alleges that Sanofi’s failure to disclose information to the FDA about harmful psychiatric side effects of the weight-loss drug Zimulti caused a drop in the company’s stock prices when the FDA declined to approve the medication. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 394</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=394</url><date>20111024164427</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>BioMedicine</link-text><url>http://www.bio-medicine.org/biology-technology-1/Shareholder-Class-Action-Filed-Against-Sanofi-Aventis-by-the-Law-Firm-of-Schiffrin-Barroway-Topaz--26-Kessler--LLP-2413-1/</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>en.sanofi-aventis.com/</link-text><url>http://en.sanofi-aventis.com/</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>sanofi aventis</normalized>\n      <tagged>Aventis</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>5013011</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>sanofi aventis</normalized>\n      <tagged>Sanofi</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>5013011</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>sanofi - synthelabo groupe</normalized>\n      <tagged>Sanofi</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>3582910</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>sanofi aventis</normalized>\n      <tagged>Sanofi-Aventis</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>5013011</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>sanofi - synthelabo groupe</normalized>\n      <tagged>Sanofi-Aventis</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>3582910</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T195723Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=295\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 295\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Target has been Criticized for using Sweatshop Labor:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> In April 2003, a federal court on the Pacific island of Saipan a\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Target has been Criticized for using Sweatshop Labor:\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt; In April 2003, a federal court on the Pacific island of Saipan a</title>\n  <description>\n    Target has been Criticized for using Sweatshop Labor:\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt; In April 2003, a federal court on the Pacific island of Saipan approved a $20 million settlement on a class action lawsuit filed against Target and 21 other companies. The lawsuit charged that the companies contracted sweatshop labor on Saipan, a U.S. Commonwealth and should be held accountable for worker treatment and conditions in foreign-owned factories operating on U.S. soil. According to the complaint, the more than 13,000 garment workers in Saipan regularly worked 12-hour days, seven days a week, often times &quot;off the clock&quot; without receiving any pay or overtime. The lawsuit also accused Levi Strauss and other companies of operating a &quot;racketeering conspiracy&quot; through which workers, who are mostly young women, sign contracts waiving their basic human rights and pay recruitment fees of up to $10,000 to secure sweatshop jobs. By agreeing to the settlement, the companies admitted no wrongdoing. &lt;/li&gt; \r\n&lt;li&gt;\r\nLee Kil-Soo, owner of the Daewoosa factory in American Samoa, was convicted in February 2003 of human trafficking for illegally confining workers in &quot;involuntary servitude,&quot; holding their passports, and threatening deportation in retaliation for any acts of non-compliance. A US Department of Labor (DOL) investigation reported that workers at Daewoosa were often beaten, deprived of food, and forced to work without pay. Clothing produced by the Daewoosa factory was sold with the &quot;Made in the USA&quot; label, because American Samoa is a US territory. Before Mr. Lee\'s arrest and the closing of the factory, Daewoosa supplied clothing to J.C. Penney, Kohl\'s, Sears, Target, and Wal-Mart. According to the Manchester Guardian Weekly, only J.C. Penney has paid back wages to the Daewoosa workers. &lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt; As of March 2001 Target was selling clothing produced at the Leader Garment factory in El Salvador. The Leader facility has been cited by the National Labor Committee as a facility that enforces mandatory pregnancy tests--women who test positive are immediately fired.  Workers must fulfill obligatory overtime of 6 days a week with 13-hour shifts, and workers are paid 60 cents an hour - less than one-third of the cost of living.&lt;/li&gt; \r\n&lt;/ul&gt; \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Business Practices | Workers Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 295</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=295</url><date>20111024164430</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>National Labor Committee</link-text><url>http://www.nlcnet.org</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.target.com</link-text><url>http://www.target.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Daewoosa</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>J.C. Penny</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Kohl\'s</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>levi strauss/ls usa menswear</normalized>\n      <tagged>Levi Strauss</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0039304</GCP>\n<GCP>0052175</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>levi strauss/ls usa jeanswear</normalized>\n      <tagged>Levi Strauss</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0039307</GCP>\n<GCP>0052177</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>levi strauss/youthwear div</normalized>\n      <tagged>Levi Strauss</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0052178</GCP></GCPs>\n   