 1999 pipe break that led to a gasoline explosion and three deaths. The pipeline break released over 200,000 gallons of gas into a creek in Washington state and fueled a fireball that fatally burned two 10-year-olds. An 18-year-old fisherman died after fumes overcame him. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    \n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 196</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=196</url><date>20111024164446</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>SFGate.com (San Francisco Chronicle)</link-text><url>http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/news/archive/2001/06/19/financial1444EDT0175.DTL</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>BP</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T202856Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=192\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 192\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In 2005, Stephen Riggio, Barnes & Noble CEO, made $2.17 million in compensation including stock option grants from the company.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In 2005, Stephen Riggio, Barnes &amp; Noble CEO, made $2.17 million in compensation including stock option grants from the company.</title>\n  <description>\n    In 2005, Stephen Riggio, Barnes &amp; Noble CEO, made $2.17 million in compensation including stock option grants from the company. From previous years, Riggio cashed out $11.16 million in stock option exercises. The Barnes &amp; Noble CEO has an additional $55.45 million in unexercised stock options from previous years. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 192</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=192</url><date>20111024164446</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission</link-text><url>http://www.aflcio.org/corporatewatch/paywatch/ceou/database.cfm?tkr=BKS&amp;pg=1</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.barnesandnoble.com</link-text><url>http://www.barnesandnoble.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Barnes &amp; Noble, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Barnes &amp; Noble</tagged>\n      <address>NY\n122 5th Ave\n10011\nNew York\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0720593</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T202949Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=288\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 288\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In June 2010, Congress assessed the oil spill action plans of the five oil giants of the United States (Exxon-Mobil, ConocoPhillip\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In June 2010, Congress assessed the oil spill action plans of the five oil giants of the United States (Exxon-Mobil, ConocoPhillip</title>\n  <description>\n    In June 2010, Congress assessed the oil spill action plans of the five oil giants of the United States (Exxon-Mobil, ConocoPhillips, Chevron, Shell, BP). All of the plans were written by the same tiny Texas subcontractor and three of them listed the phone number for the same marine science expert who died in 2005. Four plans discussed the need to protect walruses, sea lions and seals, which, as Rep. Edward J. Markey (D-Mass) dryly noted, &quot;have not called the Gulf of Mexico home for 3 million years.&quot; All five plans were over 500 pages long each yet used the same reassuring language, yet the House Energy and Commerce Chairman deemed these &quot;cookie-cutter&quot; plans as inadequate and that each of the oil giants would have been as unprepared as BP to a major oil spill such as the one in the gulf. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    \n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 288</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=288</url><date>20111024164447</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Washington Post</link-text><url>http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/06/15/AR2010061501700.html</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>BP</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>chevron usa products company</normalized>\n      <tagged>Chevron</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0611167</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>chevron u.s.a.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Chevron</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0023968</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Chevron USA Products Company</normalized>\n      <tagged>Chevron</tagged>\n      <address>CA\n6101 Bollinger Canyon Road\n94583-0804\nSan Ramon\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0611167</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Chevron U.S.A.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Chevron</tagged>\n      <address>CA\nPO BOX 2069\n94604-2069\nOakland\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0023968</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <compan