  <title>A labor dispute was settled in 2011 between British Airways executives and Unite labor union after the union organized 22 strike d</title>\n  <description>\n    A labor dispute was settled in 2011 between British Airways executives and Unite labor union after the union organized 22 strike days due to unfavorable pay freezes and restructuring of cabin procedures. The union’s strike cost the airline $240 million. British Airways reprimanded the striking workers by taking away travel concessions. The two parties were able to reach an agreement with workers agreeing to the new cabin procedures in return for pay increases. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    \n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 398</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=398</url><date>20111024164458</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Associated Press</link-text><url>http://http://finance.yahoo.com/news/British Airways-union-reach-deal-to-end-apf-2563556583.html?x=0&amp;.v=4</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>British Airways</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T213411Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=405\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 405\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Southwest began a new in-flight recycling program in 2009 with Republic Services, Inc.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Southwest began a new in-flight recycling program in 2009 with Republic Services, Inc.</title>\n  <description>\n    Southwest began a new in-flight recycling program in 2009 with Republic Services, Inc. Working with this new company allows Southwest to recycle co-mingled paper, plastic and aluminum, which makes it easier to recycle a greater volume of materials. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 405</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=405</url><date>20111024164459</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>southwest.com</link-text><url>http://www.southwest.com/html/southwest-difference/southwest-citizenship/environmental-initiatives/index.html</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.southwest.com</link-text><url>http://www.southwest.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Republic Services Inc.</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Southwest</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T213433Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=220&MajorSub=1&CompanyName=Tom%20Ford\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 220\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In March 2005, EstÃ©e Lauder and other major cosmetics manufacturers and retailers announced they would give away $175 million in p\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In March 2005, Estée Lauder and other major cosmetics manufacturers and retailers announced they would give away $175 million in p</title>\n  <description>\n    In March 2005, Estée Lauder and other major cosmetics manufacturers and retailers announced they would give away $175 million in products to settle a class-action lawsuit accusing the companies of price fixing. Under the terms of the settlement, some 39 million customers who purchased upscale cosmetics or fragrance items between May 29, 1994, and July 16, 2003, would be eligible for a free product valued between $18 and $25. Additionally, the companies agreed to pay $24 million in attorneys fees, cover related marketing and distribution costs, and not &quot;fix, establish, control or maintain the retail price at which any department store may offer for sale or sell&quot; cosmetics and fragrances. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 220</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=220&amp;MajorSub=1&amp;CompanyName=Tom%20Ford</url><date>20111024164459</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>www.elcompanies.com</link-text><url>http://www.elcompanies.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Southwest</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T213547Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=234\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 234\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In 2004, Chairman and CEO James Kilts made $29,287,926 in total compensation including stock option grants from Gillette.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>