\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=447\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 447\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In November 2008, a family at a Florida IHOP found a severed tip of a human finger in their fried chicken green salad.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In November 2008, a family at a Florida IHOP found a severed tip of a human finger in their fried chicken green salad.</title>\n  <description>\n    In November 2008, a family at a Florida IHOP found a severed tip of a human finger in their fried chicken green salad. The tip was from a cook\'s finger who had accidentally cut himself while preparing food. After being rushed to the hospital, no one could find the severed part as it had turned up on the family\'s plate of salad. The family was consequently exposed to possible health issues due to the &quot;freshly cut human flesh and blood.&quot; The lawsuit cites damages of over $15,000 but a claim letter from the family to the restaurant\'s insurance company asks for over $20 million in damages. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    \n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 447</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=447</url><date>20111024164503</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>CBS News</link-text><url>http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2010/03/03/national/main6263174.shtml</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>International House of Pancakes</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T214221Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=252\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 252\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"Ikea, Kohl\\x{2019}s and Walmart are members of 2010 Sweatshops Hall of Shame, published by International Labor Rights Forum (ILRF).\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Ikea, Kohl’s and Walmart are members of 2010 Sweatshops Hall of Shame, published by International Labor Rights Forum (ILRF).</title>\n  <description>\n    Ikea, Kohl’s and Walmart are members of 2010 Sweatshops Hall of Shame, published by International Labor Rights Forum (ILRF). These companies are on the list because of unsafe working conditions at the factory Mederes Tekstil in Denizili in Turkey. This factory produces bed linens for Ikea, Kohl’s and Walmart. Unionizing is prevented by punishment or dismissal. Four workers have died because of the unsafe working environment. Ikea, the factory’s primary buyer investigated the labor conditions in the factory and concluded that there were no major labor problems. Requests made by ILRF to work on improving the conditions in the factory have been ignored by all three companies. Read more about the 2010 Sweatshops Hall of Shame in ILRF’s report. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Business Practices | Workers Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 252</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=252</url><date>20111024164504</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>International Labor Rights Forum</link-text><url>http://http://www.laborrights.org/sites/default/files/publications-and-resources/sweatshop_hall_shame_2010.pdf</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.kohls.com</link-text><url>http://www.kohls.com</url><date></dat