lt-in-my-outback-steakhouse-potato-soup.html</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>http://www.osirestaurantpartners.com/</link-text><url>http://http://www.osirestaurantpartners.com/</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Outback Steakhouse</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T220213Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=272\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 272\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Nissan was rated as the 2nd worst polluter on the Political Economy Research Institute\\\'s (PERI) Toxic 100 index.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Nissan was rated as the 2nd worst polluter on the Political Economy Research Institute\'s (PERI) Toxic 100 index.</title>\n  <description>\n    Nissan was rated as the 2nd worst polluter on the Political Economy Research Institute\'s (PERI) Toxic 100 index. PERI is an “independent unit of the University of Massachusetts,” that promotes environmental sustainability and human rights through research. The index is based on 2007 EPA Toxics Release Inventory data. PERI\'s Toxic 100 index ranks the nation\'s largest companies based on the quantity of their emissions, relative toxicity of chemicals emitted, and proximity to population centers, among other criteria. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 272</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=272</url><date>20111024164518</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Political Economy Research Institute (PERI)</link-text><url>http://http://www.peri.umass.edu/Toxic-100-Index.430.0.html</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.nissan-global.com</link-text><url>http://www.nissan-global.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Nissan</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T220312Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=240\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 240\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In April 2007, Home Depot introduced Eco Options, a line of products that they\\\'re promoting as environmentally friendly, including\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In April 2007, Home Depot introduced Eco Options, a line of products that they\'re promoting as environmentally friendly, including</title>\n  <description>\n    In April 2007, Home Depot introduced Eco Options, a line of products that they\'re promoting as environmentally friendly, including energy efficient lightbulbs and natural insect repellants.  The line currently includes 3,000 products but Home Depot hopes to increase it to 6,000 products by 2009, which would represent 12 percent of the company\'s sales. Unlike established certification sytems for environmental products which rely on third party evaluation, Home Depot will have complete control over what can be accepted into its Eco Options line. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID