on</link-text><url>http://www.aclu.org/racialjustice/racialprofiling/25583res20020604.html</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>United Airlines</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T223413Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=240\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 240\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In 2005, Home Depot spent a total of $540,000 on lobbying expenditures and $410,000 in the 2004 election cycle.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In 2005, Home Depot spent a total of $540,000 on lobbying expenditures and $410,000 in the 2004 election cycle.</title>\n  <description>\n    In 2005, Home Depot spent a total of $540,000 on lobbying expenditures and $410,000 in the 2004 election cycle. Lobbying firms hired by Home Depot lobbied on issues such as domestic and foreign trade, superfund sites, and health issues. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 240</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=240</url><date>20111024164545</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Center for Responsive Politics</link-text><url>http://www.opensecrets.org/lobbyists/clientsum.asp?txtname=Home+Depot&amp;year=2005</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>the home depot, inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Home Depot</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0048834</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>The Home Depot, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Home Depot</tagged>\n      <address>GA\n2455 Paces Ferry Road\n30339-4024\nAtlanta\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0048834</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T223425Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=387\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 387\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Tens of thousands of workers walked off the job at several Mercedes-Benz plants across Germany in July 2004 to protest the company\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Tens of thousands of workers walked off the job at several Mercedes-Benz plants across Germany in July 2004 to protest the company</title>\n  <description>\n    Tens of thousands of workers walked off the job at several Mercedes-Benz plants across Germany in July 2004 to protest the company’s attempt to eliminate hourly breaks to try to cut labor costs. More than 20,000 workers left the assembly line at the flagship Mercedes-Benz plant in Sindelfingen alone, further intensifying the bitter dispute between the union and Daimler AG, the owner of Mercedes-Benz. The company is threatening to eliminate jobs in Sindelfingen and move production to northern Germany and South Africa, where workers do no get five-minute breaks every hour. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Business Practices | Workers Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 387</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=387</url><date>20111024164546</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>New York Times</link-text><url>http://www.nytimes.com/2004/07/16/business/dispute-disrupts-daimler-in-germany.html?n=Top%2FReference%2FTimes%20Topics%2FSubjects%2FL%2FLabor</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Daimler AG</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Mercedes-Benz</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T223444Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=240\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 240\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"Consumers filed a class-action lawsuit against Home Depot and Lowe\\x{2019}s for misleading consumers with interest-free credit promotions\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Consumers filed a class-action lawsuit against Home Depot and Lowe’s for misleading consumers with interest-free credit promotions</title>\n  <description>\n    Consumers filed a class-action lawsuit against Home Depot and Lowe’s for misleading consumers with interest-free credit promotions.  The companies were alleged to have cheated customers by applying store credit payments to interest-free balances following major promotions, leaving customers’ interest-accruing balances untouched. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    \n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 240</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=240</url><date>20111024164546</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>ConsumerAffairs.com</link-text><url>http://consumeraffairs.com/news04/home_depot_lowes.html</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>the home depot, inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Home Depot</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0048834</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>The Home Depot, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Home Depot</tagged>\n      <address>GA\n2455 Paces Ferry Road\n30339-4024\nAtlanta\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0048834</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>the home depot, inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Home Depot</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0048834</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>The Home Depot, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Home Depot</tagged>\n      <address>GA\n2455 Paces Ferry Road\n30339-4024\nAtlanta\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0048834</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T223503Z</date></review>\n    <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T223517Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=392\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 392\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In October 2008, Merck announced plans to cut 7,200 jobs, or 12 percent of its workforce.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In October 2008, Merck announced plans to cut 7,200 jobs, or 12 percent of its workforce.</title>\n  <description>\n    In October 2008, Merck announced plans to cut 7,200 jobs, or 12 percent of its workforce.  The layoffs are not in response to the financial crisis, but rather the result of falling drug and vaccine sales.  As their patents expire, large pharmaceutical companies are faced with skyrocketing competition from cheap generics.  The job cuts are expected to save the company up to $4.2 billion in operating costs over the next four years, though they will need to spend up to $2 billion in reorganization and severance costs. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 392</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=392</url><date>20111024164547</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>New York Times</link-text><url>http://www.nytimes.com/2008/10/23/business/23merck.html?scp=2&amp;sq=merck&amp;st=cse</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>merck pharmaceutical (hk) ltd</normalized>\n      <tagged>Merck</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>4897016</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n    \n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=208&MajorSub=1&CompanyName=Dodge\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 208\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Chryser received a summary score of 43 out of 100 in a 2006 Ceres report examining companies\\\' response to the issue of climate cha\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Chryser received a summary score of 43 out of 100 in a 2006 Ceres report examining companies\' response to the issue of climate cha</title>\n  <description>\n    Chryser received a summary score of 43 out of 100 in a 2006 Ceres report examining companies\' response to the issue of climate change. Ceres is a national network of environmental activists and investors working together to address climate change issues. While Chrysler has made incremental improvements in its fleet fuel efficiency, the company is only striving to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by 10% from 2002 to 2012. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 208</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=208&amp;MajorSub=1&amp;CompanyName=Dodge</url><date>20111024164547</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>CERES</link-text><url>http://www.ceres.org/pub/docs/Ceres_corp_gov_and_climate_change_0306.pdf</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Chrysler</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T223554Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=259&MajorSub=1&CompanyName=Victoria%27s%20Secret%20%28Limited%20Brands%20subsidiary%29\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 259\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'The US Green Building Council awarded the Bath and Body Works headquarters and distribution center a LEED Silver certification, in\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>The US Green Building Council awarded the Bath and Body Works headquarters and distribution center a LEED Silver certification, in</title>\n  <description>\n    The US Green Building Council awarded the Bath and Body Works headquarters and distribution center a LEED Silver certification, in the category of Existing Building: Operations and Maintenance (EB O&amp;M). Bath and Body Works is the first Limited Brands building to earn LEED Certification and is the first and only building in Ohio to earn the LEED EB O&amp;M Silver Certification. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 259</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=259&amp;MajorSub=1&amp;CompanyName=Victoria%27s%20Secret%20%28Limited%20Brands%20subsidiary%29</url><date>20111024164548</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Bath &amp; Body Works</link-text><url>http://http://www.bathandbodyworksathome.com/responsibility/environment/news_item/10-03-03/Limited_Brands_First_in_Ohio_to_Earn_LEED_EB_O_M_Silver_Certification.aspx</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Bath and Body Works, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Bath and Body Works</tagged>\n      <address>OH\nSeven Limited Parkway\n43068\nReynoldsburg\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0637295</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Limited Brands</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T223629Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=405\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 405\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"\\x{2022} In March 2007, Southwest Airlines reported to the Federal Aviation Administration that it had failed complete several fuselage i\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>• In March 2007, Southwest Airlines reported to the Federal Aviation Administration that it had failed complete several fuselage i</title>\n  <description>\n    • In March 2007, Southwest Airlines reported to the Federal Aviation Administration that it had failed complete several fuselage inspections. Instead of grounding the planes until inspection could be completed, Southwest Airlines continued to fly the planes. In addition, evidence has came forward that indicates that Southwest was working with FAA agents to keep their error unknown. Currently, the Federal Aviation Administration is fining Southwest Airlines $10.2. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Human Rights | Health and Wellness</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 405</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=405</url><date>20111024164548</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>National Public Radio (NPR)</link-text><url>http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=89328997</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Southwest Airlines</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T223739Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=392\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 392\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Over 2,000 residents of Merced, California filed a lawsuit in Federal court against the operators of a local manufacturing plant t\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Over 2,000 residents of Merced, California filed a lawsuit in Federal court against the operators of a local manufacturing plant t</title>\n  <description>\n    Over 2,000 residents of Merced, California filed a lawsuit in Federal court against the operators of a local manufacturing plant that they say contaminated their drinking water with the cancer-causing chemical Chromium 6.  The plant was operated by a subsidiary of Merck &amp; Co, Inc and Amsted Industries, and built industrial cooling towers from 1961 to 1994.  The lawsuit alleges that the plant’s operators knew of the contamination long before the information became public.  One of the residents involved in the suit had a fibroid tumor removed in from her stomach in the 1990s; she also said that twenty other people in the neighborhood either had cancer or died from it.  Lawyers for Merck and Amsted say that the companies are spending $38 million to clean up the site, and that there is no evidence that the plant contaminated water and caused residents to become sick. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 392</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=392</url><date>20111024164549</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>SFGate.com (San Francisco Chronicle)</link-text><url>http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2008/12/21/MNQI14RH6V.DTL&amp;hw=feinstein+boxer&amp;sn=001&amp;sc=1000</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Amsted Industries/plexco Div.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Amsted Industries</tagged>\n      <address>IL\nTwo Prudential Plaza\n180 North Stetson Street, Suite 1800\n60601\nChicago\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0662039</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Merck &amp; Co Inc</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T223919Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=190\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 190\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In August 2003 <I>The Wall Street Journal </I> reported that Bank of America and at least nine other US banks moved more than $17 \'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In August 2003 &lt;I&gt;The Wall Street Journal &lt;/I&gt; reported that Bank of America and at least nine other US banks moved more than $17 </title>\n  <description>\n    In August 2003 &lt;I&gt;The Wall Street Journal &lt;/I&gt; reported that Bank of America and at least nine other US banks moved more than $17 billion into investment funds to shelter hundreds of millions of dollars from state taxes, sparking probes by state tax authorities. The banks created funds that did not publicly sell shares but paid tax-exempt dividends to the banks, according to the report. Securities and Exchange Commission records show Bank of America transferred at least $8 billion into its fund, which sheltered more than $750 million in income. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 190</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=190</url><date>20111024164550</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Common Dreams Newswire</link-text><url>http://www.commondreams.org/headlines03/0807-05.htm</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.bankofamerica.com</link-text><url>http://www.bankofamerica.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Bank of America</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T223958Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=226\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 226\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In 2001, twenty-six state attorney generals asked Ford to remove mercury switches from their vehicles due the toxic persistent nat\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In 2001, twenty-six state attorney generals asked Ford to remove mercury switches from their vehicles due the toxic persistent nat</title>\n  <description>\n    In 2001, twenty-six state attorney generals asked Ford to remove mercury switches from their vehicles due the toxic persistent nature of mercury and its vapors. Although General Motors and DaimlerChrysler were also cited as continuing to use mercury compounds in car manufacturing, Ford was the only vehicle manufacturer to receive the request. &quot;Ford is in the early stages of a very large recall of vehicles,&quot; said a press aide to New York Attorney General Eliot Spitzer, who signed the letter. &quot;The timing would be right for Ford to replace a large number of mercury switches, as it will be recalling about 3 million cars due to potentially faulty tires.&quot; Environmental Defense\'s Clean Car Campaign estimates there are 200 tons of mercury in cars and trucks currently on the road. &lt;/li&gt; \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Human Rights | Health and Wellness</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 226</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=226</url><date>20111024164550</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    \n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>ford motor co/parts   service</normalized>\n      <tagged>Ford</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0031508</GCP>\n<GCP>0084422</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>ford motor company/special vehicle oper.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Ford</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0756122</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T224020Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=201\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 201\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"Chevron was ranked the seventh \\x{201c}greenest\\x{201d} oil company out of the top 10 leading US oil corporations by Greenopia in 2011.\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Chevron was ranked the seventh “greenest” oil company out of the top 10 leading US oil corporations by Greenopia in 2011.</title>\n  <description>\n    Chevron was ranked the seventh “greenest” oil company out of the top 10 leading US oil corporations by Greenopia in 2011. Chevron’s sustainability reporting is missing a lot of data but still forms a decent report. Chevron has also greatly reduced its greenhouse gas emissions from the year before but when scaled to its production, the rates are only moderately efficient. Chevron was also considered average in terms of the volume of oil spilled in 2009 but Chevron had a total of 798 oil spills in 2009, one of the largest numbers reported by any of the companies. Even when this number was normalized, Chevron is still among the worst although the amount of oil spilled was about average. Greenopia also notes the recent multi-billion dollar fine Chevron has received for its environmental disaster in Ecuador, although absorbed by its purchase of Texaco. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 201</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=201</url><date>20111024164551</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Greenopia</link-text><url>http://http://www.greenopia.com/usa/oil_listing.aspx?ID=8&amp;input=Name-or-product&amp;Listpage=0 </url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.chevron.com</link-text><url>http://www.chevron.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>chevron usa products company</normalized>\n      <tagged>Chevron</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0611167</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>chevron u.s.a.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Chevron</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0023968</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Chevron USA Products Company</normalized>\n      <tagged>Chevron</tagged>\n      <address>CA\n6101 Bollinger Canyon Road\n94583-0804\nSan Ramon\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0611167</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Chevron U.S.A.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Chevron</tagged>\n      <address>CA\nPO BOX 2069\n94604-2069\nOakland\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0023968</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Chevron Oil Co</normalized>\n      <tagged>Chevron</tagged>\n      <address>CA\n225 Bust St\nPO Box 3495\n94104\nSan Francisco\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0072544</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>texaco inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Texaco</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0076568</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T224027Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=200\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 200\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'An affidavit released by Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) in March 2009 alleged that the Cargill Meat Solutions plant in \'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>An affidavit released by Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) in March 2009 alleged that the Cargill Meat Solutions plant in </title>\n  <description>\n    An affidavit released by Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) in March 2009 alleged that the Cargill Meat Solutions plant in Dayton, Virginia knowingly hired around 400 “unauthorized and smuggled aliens.” The affidavit was used to secure a search warrant for a March 2008 raid of the plant after it was found that nearly one third of the 1,300 I-9 employment forms submitted to the Department of Homeland Security by Cargill were suspected to have been filled out using “fraudulently obtained or invalid documents.” ICE investigators also found evidence that pregnant women were also treated differently in the plant, being forced to work up until they gave birth and made to start working again soon after delivery. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Business Practices | Workers Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 200</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=200</url><date>20111024165107</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>WHSV</link-text><url>http://www.whsv.com/news/headlines/4343