0886549</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>PT Nikomas Gemilang</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T230413Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=458\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 458\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"Men\\x{2019}s Health gives The Cheesecake Factory an \\x{201c}F\\x{201d} in its \\x{201c}Eat This, Not That\\x{201d} series in which it rates fast-food chain restaurants \"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Men’s Health gives The Cheesecake Factory an “F” in its “Eat This, Not That” series in which it rates fast-food chain restaurants </title>\n  <description>\n    Men’s Health gives The Cheesecake Factory an “F” in its “Eat This, Not That” series in which it rates fast-food chain restaurants on transparency in nutritional information and the availability of healthy menu options. Men’s Health notes that the restaurant chain still refuses to provide nutritional information online but that the numbers are now available due to a recent California state law. Judging by the numbers, Men’s Health boldly names The Cheesecake Factory as the “Worst Restaurant in America” due to its “atrocious lineup of menu items.” The magazine advises to avoid the “Factory Combinations” as none of the two-meat dishes on this part of the menu contains less than 2,000 calories or 50 grams of saturated fat. Even if you split the “least terrible” of these dishes, the Chicken Madeira and Herb Crusted Salmon, you’re still consuming more calories than a Chili Cheese Dog and large fries from Dairy Queen. Other plates to avoid include the Ranch House Burger (1,941 calories), the healthy sounding Grilled Chicken and Avocado Club (1,752 calories) and the innocent sounding side of Macaroni and Cheese (1,462 calories). \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Human Rights | Health and Wellness</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 458</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=458</url><date>20111024164612</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Men\'s Health</link-text><url>http://http://eatthis.menshealth.com/restaurants/cheesecake-factory</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.thecheesecakefactory.com </link-text><url>http://www.thecheesecakefactory.com </url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>The Cheesecake Factory Bakery, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>The Cheesecake Factory</tagged>\n      <address>CA\n26950 Agoura Rd\n91301\nCalabasas Hills\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0785397</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>International Dairy Queen, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Dairy Queen</tagged>\n      <address>MN\nP.O. Box 390286\n55439-0286\nMinneapolis\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0073245</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T230512Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=269&MajorSub=1&CompanyName=Wonka\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 269\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'According to South Africa-based global anti-poverty group, ActionAid International, approximately 50,000 Brazilian dairy farmers h\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>According to South Africa-based global anti-poverty group, ActionAid International, approximately 50,000 Brazilian dairy farmers h</title>\n  <description>\n    According to South Africa-based global anti-poverty group, ActionAid International, approximately 50,000 Brazilian dairy farmers have been forced out of business as a result of aggressive takeovers by Nestlé and Parmalat.  \r\n&lt;p&gt;\r\nIn Peru, Nestlé controls 80 percent of the nation\'s milk production. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 269</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=269&amp;MajorSub=1&amp;CompanyName=Wonka</url><date>20111024164613</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>ActionAid</link-text><url>http://www.actionaid.org.uk/1489/press_release.html</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>International Dairy Queen, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Dairy Queen</tagged>\n      <address>MN\nP.O. Box 390286\n55439-0286\nMinneapolis\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0073245</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>parmalat usa corp.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Parmalat</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0024321</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T230608Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=229&MajorSub=1&CompanyName=Old%20Navy\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 229\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"The National Labor Committee\\x{2019}s May 2006 report entitled \\x{201c}US-Jordan Free Trade Agreement Descends into Human Trafficking & Involunt\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>The National Labor Committee’s May 2006 report entitled “US-Jordan Free Trade Agreement Descends into Human Trafficking &amp; Involunt</title>\n  <description>\n    The National Labor Committee’s May 2006 report entitled “US-Jordan Free Trade Agreement Descends into Human Trafficking &amp; Involuntary Servitude,” documented a series of worker rights’ violations at Gap supplier Western Factory. The lack of respect for labor rights included the following:&lt;p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Human trafficking and involuntary servitude of guest workers&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Confiscation of passports and denial of identification cards&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Mandatory 16 to 20 hour shifts. Typical work weeks consisted of 109 hours&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Wages below the legal minimum. Workers were cheated of 65 percent of the wages legally owed to them&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Six months of withheld wages&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Inadequate and unsanitary working conditions&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;Routine beatings and threats for production mistakes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;The NLC also reported that factory management sexually abused four young girls, including a 16 year-old. Management falsely promised attractive, young women better jobs, higher wages and less work. Management told the girls they wanted to take them on a day trip around Jordan. Instead, the young women were brought to a hotel where the managers forced themselves on the girls.\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;In a July 2006 urgent update, the NLC reported that Western Factory management allegedly beat workers for requesting payment of back wages owed to them. Additionally, the management cut off food and water to the workers’ dorm. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    \n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 229</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=229&amp;MajorSub=1&amp;CompanyName=Old%20Navy</url><date>20111024164613</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>National Labor Committee</link-text><url>http://www.nlcnet.org/article.php?id=10</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>The Gap, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>The Gap</tagged>\n      <address>CA\n2 Folsom St\n94105\nSan Francisco\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0677681</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Western Factory</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T231824Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=226\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 226\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Ford received a perfect 100 on the Human Rights Campaign 2008 Corporate Equality Index which rates large corporations on policies \'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Ford received a perfect 100 on the Human Rights Campaign 2008 Corporate Equality Index which rates large corporations on policies </title>\n  <description>\n    Ford received a perfect 100 on the Human Rights Campaign 2008 Corporate Equality Index which rates large corporations on policies that affect their gay, lesbian, bisexual and transgender employees, consumers and investors. The HRC Corporate Equality Index rates companies on a scale of 0 to 100 percent. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    \n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 226</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=226</url><date>20111024164614</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Human Rights Campaign</link-text><url>http://www.hrc.org/issues/ceihome.asp </url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>ford motor co/parts   service</normalized>\n      <tagged>Ford</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0031508</GCP>\n<GCP>0084422</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>ford motor company/special vehicle oper.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Ford</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0756122</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T231848Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=412&MajorSub=1&CompanyName=Tanqueray\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 412\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"\\x{2022} The CSR department of Diageo is working to make sure that their business does not support human rights violations.\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>• The CSR department of Diageo is working to make sure that their business does not support human rights violations.</title>\n  <description>\n    • The CSR department of Diageo is working to make sure that their business does not support human rights violations. Currently, Diageo operates out of over 180 countries many of which have human rights violations including: Kenya, Tanzania, Mexico, Colombia, Peru, Brazil, Ghana, Russia, Turkey, the Ivory Coast, and India. To make sure Diageo does not play a part in these violations, the CSR department of Diageo created a human rights policy with the help of  Amnesty International. Diageo feels the best way they can promote change is to create breweries in these countries that can provide good jobs. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Human Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 412</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=412&amp;MajorSub=1&amp;CompanyName=Tanqueray</url><date>20111024164615</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Guardian</link-text><url>http://www.guardian.co.uk/society/2003/nov/17/19</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.diageo.com</link-text><url>http://www.diageo.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Diageo North America</normalized>\n      <tagged>Diageo</tagged>\n      <address>CT\n801 Main Ave\n06851\nNorwalk\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0080720</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Diageo North America</normalized>\n      <tagged>Diageo</tagged>\n      <address>CT\n801 Main Ave\n06851\nNorwalk\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0080720</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Diageo North America</normalized>\n      <tagged>Diageo</tagged>\n      <address>CT\n801 Main Ave\n06851\nNorwalk\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0080720</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Diageo North America</normalized>\n      <tagged>Diageo</tagged>\n      <address>CT\n801 Main Ave\n06851\nNorwalk\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0080720</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Diageo Guinness USA Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Diageo</tagged>\n      <address>CT\n801 Main Avenue\n06851\nNorwalk\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0083820</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Diageo North America</normalized>\n      <tagged>Diageo</tagged>\n      <address>CT\n801 Main Ave\n06851\nNorwalk\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0080720</G