ties and Exchange Commission (SEC) began requiring disclosure of voting policy data in 2003. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 303</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=303</url><date>20111024164621</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    \n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Vanguard Group</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T233608Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=287\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 287\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Sempra Energy paid $5.7 million to the customers of its San Diego Gas & Electric Co.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Sempra Energy paid $5.7 million to the customers of its San Diego Gas &amp; Electric Co.</title>\n  <description>\n    Sempra Energy paid $5.7 million to the customers of its San Diego Gas &amp; Electric Co. subsidiary to end a lawsuit filed by State Attorney General Bill Lockyer and the California Public Utilities Commission. According to the lawsuit, Sempra was responsible for the shortfall in natural gas, which caused SDG&amp;E to cut gas supplies to major customers for 17 days in 2000-2001. This action disrupted service, raised energy prices, and forced power plants to use more polluting fuels. The settlement money will be used to reduce the cost of buying power for its 1 million electricity customers. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 287</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=287</url><date>20111024164622</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>San Diego Union-Tribune</link-text><url>http://www.signonsandiego.com/uniontrib/20061014/news_1b14sempra.html</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.sempra.com</link-text><url>http://www.sempra.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>San Diego Gas &amp; Electric Co.</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>Sempra Energy</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111023T233756Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=201\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 201\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Six protesters were shot and killed at a Chevron Texaco oil export terminal in Nigeria on February 1, 2005.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Six protesters were shot and killed at a Chevron Texaco oil export terminal in Nigeria on February 1, 2005.</title>\n  <description>\n    Six protesters were shot and killed at a Chevron Texaco oil export terminal in Nigeria on February 1, 2005.  Hundreds of protesters arrived at the terminal to oppose the lack of development and jobs in the community of Ugborodo when security forces opened fire on the people.  Nigerian National Petroleum Corp. and Chevron operate the facility as part of a joint venture between the oil giant and