n spearheaded by the National Writers Union, focused on ending Time Warner’s manipulation of free-lance journalists.  The Stop AOL Time Warner Campaign sought to educate journalists and the public on the exploitative nature of “work-for-hire” contracts, which strip journalists of all rights to their work while simultaneously leaving them open to any liability.  Time Warner is accused of pressuring free-lance journalists to sign such agreements or lose employment. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    \n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 345</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=345</url><date>20111024164639</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>National Writers Union</link-text><url>http://http://www.nwu.org/nwu/index.php?cmd=showPage&amp;page_id=1.5.2.2.6</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Time Warner Cable</normalized>\n      <tagged>Time Warner</tagged>\n      <address>MN\n9705 Data Park\n55343-9119 \nMinnetonka\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>083633600</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Time Warner Interactive Group</normalized>\n      <tagged>Time Warner</tagged>\n      <address>NY\n1 Time Warner Center\n10019 \nNew York\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0099171</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n    \n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=251\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 251\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'In 2004 Kmart paid $60,000 to settle charges by the U.S.\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In 2004 Kmart paid $60,000 to settle charges by the U.S.</title>\n  <description>\n    In 2004 Kmart paid $60,000 to settle charges by the U.S. Equal Employment Opportunity Commission alleging the company violated the Americans with Disabilities Act by refusing to hire a man because of his mental disability.  Edward Jones, 35, is mildly mentally retarded but qualified to perform the duties of stocker, the EEOC suit said. The lawsuit claimed that he scored higher on Kmart\'s pre-employment questionnaire than applicants later hired for the job. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Politics</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 251</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=251</url><date>20111024164639</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Oakland Press</link-text><url>http://www.theoaklandpress.com/stories/031304/bus_20040313008.shtml</url><date></date></link><link><link-text>www.kmartcorp.com</link-text><url>http://www.kmartcorp.com</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>kmart corporation</normalized>\n      <tagged>Kmart</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0072000</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111024T001010Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=196\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 196\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"BP was ranked the fourth \\x{201c}greenest\\x{201d} oil company out of the top 10 leading US oil corporations by Greenopia in 2011.\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>BP was ranked the fourth “greenest” oil company out of the top 10 leading US oil corporations by Greenopia in 2011.</title>\n  <description>\n    BP was ranked the fourth “greenest” oil company out of the top 10 leading US oil corporations by Greenopia in 2011. Greenopia commends BP’s sustainability report as one of the best in thoroughness and transparency; BP has also been decreasing its emissions per unit of production and when compared to its volume of production, BP is one of the more efficient companies. However, BP’s Deepwater Horizon Oil Spill was arguably one of the worst man-made disasters of all time, especially as the catastrophe could have been avoided and BP was somewhat negligent in handling the situation. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    \n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 196</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=196</url><date>20111024164640</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Greenopia</link-text><url>http://http://www.greenopia.com/usa/oil_listing.aspx?ID=1&amp;input=Name-or-product&amp;Listpage=0</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized></normalized>\n      <tagged>BP</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111024T001355Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=222\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 222\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Although many retailers started pulling business out of Burma in recognition of the widespread human rights violations by the coun\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Although many retailers started pulling business out of Burma in recognition of the widespread human rights violations by the coun</title>\n  <description>\n    Although many retailers started pulling business out of Burma in recognition of the widespread human rights violations by the country\'s ruling military junta, Federated Department Stores had ties to Burma until early 2003. &lt;p&gt;In July 2003, Congress made it illegal to import garments from Burma into the United States. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Human Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 222</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=222</url><date>20111024164641</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Campaign for Labor Rights</link-text><url>http://www.clrlabor.org/alerts/2003/Mar14-DurBurma.htm#burma</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>Federated Department Stores, Inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Federated Department Stores</tagged>\n      <address>NY\n1440 Broadway\n10018\nNew York\nUnited States</address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0084827</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111024T001428Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=301&MajorSub=1&CompanyName=Wright\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 301\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Tyson is involved in at least six lawsuits over allegations that it doesn\\\'t pay its workers for the time it takes to get ready for\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Tyson is involved in at least six lawsuits over allegations that it doesn\'t pay its workers for the time it takes to get ready for</title>\n  <description>\n    Tyson is involved in at least six lawsuits over allegations that it doesn\'t pay its workers for the time it takes to get ready for and after their shifts.\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;In 1998, workers at Tyson\'s Corydon, Indiana poultry plant filed a half million dollar lawsuit against the company after the Department of Labor determined that workers were being cheated out of 30 minutes of overtime pay each day.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;In 1999, 11 employees sued Tyson Foods in an attempt to collect the overtime they claim they are owed. The pay was for the time employees at the  Albertville, Alabama plant spent gathering and putting on his protective gear and sanitizing equipment before and after work and for breaks. As of 2004 the suit was being considered for class-action status&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;\r\nThe Labor Department Solicitor\'s Office sued Tyson in 2002 seeking back wages and damages for current and former employees at the company\'s Blountsville, Alabama plant. The Labor Department also is trying to get a court order to force Tyson to pay all its employees for time spent putting on the protective gear and for cleaning up at the end of the day.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;li&gt;In 2001 Tyson  appealed a ruling involving more than 800 IBP workers who weren\'t paid while they were getting their protective gear on and sharpening their knives for the production line.\r\nThe plaintiffs received a judgment of $3.2 million from the U.S. District Court in Washington, and their attorneys won about $1.2 million to cover the cost of fees.&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt; \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Business Practices | Workers Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 301</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=301&amp;MajorSub=1&amp;CompanyName=Wright</url><date>20111024164641</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    \n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normali