t will no longer buy palm oil from Sinar Mas or its subsidiaries because SMART, one of\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Burger King pledged in September 2010 that it will no longer buy palm oil from Sinar Mas or its subsidiaries because SMART, one of</title>\n  <description>\n    Burger King pledged in September 2010 that it will no longer buy palm oil from Sinar Mas or its subsidiaries because SMART, one of the company’s subsidiaries, has destroyed rainforests and carbon-dense peatlands in Borneo and Sumatra. Greenpeace claims that Sinar Mas is destroying the rainforest, endangering orangutans and reducing carbon dioxide sinks. Others that have stopped buying from Sinar Mas, one of the biggest producers of palm oil, or other suppliers associated with deforestation include Unilever, Nestle, Cadbury and Kraft. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 197</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=197</url><date>20111024164647</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Environmental Leader</link-text><url>http://www.environmentalleader.com/2010/09/03/burger-king-dumps-palm-oil-supplier-over-land-use-practices/</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>burger king corporation</normalized>\n      <tagged>Burger King</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0675258</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>cadbury confectionery ltd</normalized>\n      <tagged>Cadbury</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>9400550</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>kraft foods, inc.</normalized>\n      <tagged>Kraft</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0021000</GCP>\n<GCP>0025400</GCP>\n<GCP>0043000</GCP>\n<GCP>0070277</GCP>\n<GCP>0074