enerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Disney paid $903,000 to the State of California in December 2001 after one of its contractors violated child labor, minimum wage, \'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Disney paid $903,000 to the State of California in December 2001 after one of its contractors violated child labor, minimum wage, </title>\n  <description>\n    Disney paid $903,000 to the State of California in December 2001 after one of its contractors violated child labor, minimum wage, and overtime laws while producing toys. The contractor, KTBA Inc., paid workers $1.20 per hour, while the state minimum wage was $6.25. State officials found workers violating state law by assembling tiaras and wands for children from their homes, and minors from 7 through 15 assembling products (minimum age is 16). KTBA, which has since gone out of business, owes workers $1.5 million, to be distributed by Disney. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Business Practices | Workers Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 213</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=213</url><date>20111024164649</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>California Labor Commissioner Bulletin</link-text><url>http://www.dir.ca.gov/dirnews/2001/IR2001-11.html</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>the walt disney company italia spa - div. bvhe</normalized>\n      <tagged>Disney</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>8007038</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>walt disney book publishing group</normalized>\n      <tagged>Disney</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0725961</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>walt disney computer software</normalized>\n      <tagged>Disney</tagged>\n      <address