uses continue.  Kmart is one of many prominent retailers that continue to purchase denim clothing from Tarrant, despite such reports. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Business Practices | Workers Rights</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 251</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=251</url><date>20111024164700</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>Sweatshop Watch</link-text><url>http://www.sweatshopwatch.org/media/pdf/newsletters/9_3.pdf</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>kmart corporation</normalized>\n      <tagged>Kmart</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0072000</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111024T004034Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=187\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 187\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \'Archer Daniels Midland, the largest U.S. producer of ethanol, uses coal to generate the power used to produce ethanol at its proce\'\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>Archer Daniels Midland, the largest U.S. producer of ethanol, uses coal to generate the power used to produce ethanol at its proce</title>\n  <description>\n    Archer Daniels Midland, the largest U.S. producer of ethanol, uses coal to generate the power used to produce ethanol at its processing plants in Decatur, Illinois, Columbus, Nebraska, and Cedar Rapids and Clinton, Iowa.  Coal-fired power generation spews carcinogenic pollutants and greenhouse gases into the atmosphere, making the ‘green’ label applied to ethanol a misnomer.  Additionally, the biofuel plants themselves emit high levels of carbon monoxide, methanol, and volatile organic compounds.  A report published by the EPA found that ADM’s ethanol plant in Clinton alone emitted almost 20,000 tons of pollutants in 2004, including sulfur dioxide and nitrogen oxides. \n\n  </description>\n  <categories>\n    <category>\n      <category-name>Environment</category-name>\n    </category>\n  </categories>\n  <source>\n    <link><link-text>Green America: Company ID 187</link-text><url>http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=187</url><date>20111024164701</date></link>\n  </source>\n  <links>\n    <link><link-text>CorpWatch</link-text><url>http://www.corpwatch.org/article.php?id=13646</url><date></date></link>\n  </links>\n  <companies>\n   <company>\n      <normalized>archer daniels midland company</normalized>\n      <tagged>Archer Daniels Midland</tagged>\n      <address></address>\n      <GCPs><GCP>0716071</GCP></GCPs>\n    </company>\n  </companies>\n  <reviews>\n        <review><reviewer>insight</reviewer><date>20111024T004057Z</date></review>\n\n  </reviews>\n </evidence>'),('$VAR1 = [\n          bless( {\n                   \'URL\' => \'http://www.greenamerica.org/programs/responsibleshopper/company.cfm?id=253&MajorSub=1&CompanyName=Wheat%20Thins\',\n                   \'SourceText\' => \'Green America: Company ID 253\'\n                 }, \'Com::elle::bLeaf::EvidenceGenerator::NewsSource\' ),\n          \"In 2002, Kraft donated \\$ 161,000 to defeat Oregon\\x{2019}s Measure 27, which would have required labeling of GMO food on products sold in\"\n        ];\n',' <evidence>\n  <title>In 2002, Kraft donated $ 161,000 to defeat Oregon’s Measure 27, which would have required labeling of GMO food on products sold in</title>\n  <description>\n    In 2002, Kraft donated $ 161,000 to defeat Oregon’s Measure 27, which would have required labeling of GMO food on products sold in that state \n\n  